Rating: 3
I made this recipe with the suggestions of others, using all green cabbage instead of green & red, throwing a cheese rind in while the soup simmered, using chicken stock instead of vegetable stock, and skipping the bread, but still found the soup to be a bit bland. I found that adding a teaspoon or two of sugar did the trick, though--just like you would add to a fresh a tomato sauce to pique the flavors. I also topped the soup with fresh basil (in addition to the cooked basil), parmesan, fresh black pepper, and extra virgen olive oil after plating, and found that that enlivened the dish nicely. Be careful about adding the parmesan to the soup before it's had a chance to cool down to serving temperature. If the soup is too hot it will melt the parmesan, creating a weird stringy texture in the soup.

