Here's my comments on this soup (having made it for the first time tonight): 1/ Make 1/2 the recipe the first time, it's designed to feed TWELVE. If you don't like it, less to throw out. 2/ Don't use the red cabbage. I hesitated seriously before adding, and then kind of regretted it. It doesn't ruin the soup, I just have a hunch the actual recipe (don't we wish we could have it) does not include that. 3/ Slice any cabbage that you do put it in very, very thin strips. Cabbage is not appealing in soups and you want to kind of camoflage. 4/ This recipe needs either more salt (a lot more) or bouillion cubes. And definitely use chicken broth or a combination of chicken/vegetable. If you do the above, it's actually quite, quite good.

