Rating: 4
I love this recipe and had fun preparing it! Made some changes! To make beans more digestible, changed the soak water around every hour 3-4 times, then placed a strip of kombu (kelp, a sea vegetable) on bottom of bowl with beans on top, then final soak water, cover, refrigerate two days. Drain beans. Cut up kombu into tiny squares and set aside (add with beans.) Used 12 qt. pot; extra virgin olive oil; five UNSALTED vegetable cubes (Morga) softened in 1 qt boiling water before adding. Unsalted is key here. Salt used before beans are fully cooked can make them tough. Also added tomatoes with red cabbage and zucchini for the same reason. I like beans soft! Added water as I went along so as to always keep everything covered and just enough to ALMOST cover at the end. Cooked beans 1-1/2 hours before proceeding. Weighed almost everything! Carrots, celery 12-oz each; potatoes (Yukon Gold), tomatoes, white and red cabbages, zucchini 1 to 1-1/4# each. (If using large garden variety of zucchini, remove seeds and the soft pithy part in center.) At the end, I took out 3 ladles-full of liquid and added one packet vegetable Miso-Cup Soup to compensate for additional water and salt needed. Did not use additional oil or bread suggested. Parmesan a must; added individually! Enjoy!

